The paper deals with capacity upper bounds for channels with insertions and deletions, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses techniques from convex programming and real analysis, which are commonly used in computer science theory (cs.DS) and computational mathematics (cs.NA). The paper also discusses novel probability distributions and special functions, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and mathematical analysis (cs.CC).
